<TITLE> BTCL launches unlimited broadband package </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 04 (bdnews4.com)  Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Ltd (BTCL) will be providing unlimited broadband internet service for as low as Tk 300 per month. According to a statement on Monday, subscribers will be able to talk and browse the internet (unlimited browsing) using a single ADSL connection. The asymmetric digital subscriber line (ADSL) is a type of broadband communications technology that allows more data to be sent through existing copper telephone lines compared to traditional lines. A special filter, called a microfilter, allows both voice (telephone) and internet services simultaneously. The BTCL is offering several unlimited packages. The following websites have further details: www.btcl.gov.bd, www.bcube.net.bd and www.ememsystems.net. bdnew
